  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "LARRY POGIR",
    "text": "All right. I'm Larry, the middle grandson. Practically Darren has said everything that I wanted to say. I'd just like to say-- I mean, I'll repeat a couple of things-- that Motel is a very special man. It has been great having him as my grandfather. Sitting down and listening to the stories has been a wonderful experience. Listening to Selwyn and Rubin on several occasions has also been great, a very good learning experience. And however, it is very difficult for me to understand certain things that they did go through. But all I can say is that it was very had times. And as Joy just said, it must never be forgotten. And I just want to say that I love Motel. And as Darren and everybody said to Ida, who went through everything with Motel, she mustn't be forgotten. And that's it.",
